Final: There are more indictments coming out of DC and Columbia than good ideas these days. It’s time to overhaul the system that allows it.
10. Ban fundraising while Congress is in session. Members should be working while in DC. Instead of fundraisers, spend time reading bills.
9. Ban roll-over campaign dollars. Require fed candidates to zero-out their campaign accounts after each cycle. If unopposed, must return $.
8. One person, one pension. Ban politicians from double dipping and receiving multiple pensions at one time for separate political offices.
7. Real-time campaign account monitoring. Candidates use central bank for campaign accts so public can view donations/spending in real time.
6. Close the revolving door. Increase the wait period for former members of Congress to become lobbyists from 1 year to 5 years.
5. Pass the DISCLOSE Act. Close loopholes by requiring full disclosure for special interests who hide behind Super PACs.
4. Automatic voter registration. Corruption feeds off of apathy. Voters should be automatically registered on their 18th birthday.
3. End gerrymandering. Create indep. commissions to draw district lines. Voters should pick their politicians, not the other way around.
2. Ban PAC contributions. It’s time to weaken the overwhelming political power of special interests.
1. Term limits for all members of Congress. 3 terms for House, 2 terms for Senate. No more career politicians.
